metadata.name: Possible Ways #6
metadata.description:
This project is written in javascript without using any other libraries, and it is an endless real-time software animation.

The appearance of each token is initially determined by the hash, but the size and positions of its elements change randomly over time, creating an infinite performance.

While working on this project, I was inspired by the elusiveness of the moment, that cannot be saved or predicted. It can only be experienced.

metadata.name: Winesburg, Ohio #81
metadata.description: “Winesburg, Ohio” is an act of uncanny place-making. The collection borrows its name from a 1919 short-story cycle by Sherwood Anderson, which explores a peculiar cast of characters living within a fictionalized, midwestern town. Like Anderson’s text, the “Winesburg, Ohio” algorithm constructs a world through recurring portrayals of specific structures and landmarks. Its scenes are populated by a variety of familiar elements taken from my larger body of work, including water towers, houses, and churches. Meanwhile, a series of scripted gestures insert abstract compositional elements into the outputs, counteracting their pictorial legibility. The strange landscapes that result are composite ideograms, comprised of multiple spatial possibilities that co-exist in varying states of contradiction.

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #190
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Adventure #34
metadata.description:
‘Adventure’, inspired by ‘Soundscape’ of ‘The Paper Crane’, brings to fxhash the recreation of landscapes with the use of the lines.

What are the lines?

A line is a continuous brand with a longer length than width, made on a surface, by a moving point. It's one of the seven basic elements of art.

How can the lines be?

Lines can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal; straight or curves, thick or thin. But also simple or single-trace, perceived by a glance or composed of fragments of two or more lines, which to visualize them must displace our eyes in several directions.

Artwork (PNG layers). Randomization is powered by PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Psy Sym Blotter #2
metadata.description:
Psychedelic Symmetrical Blotter art generator with interactive drawing functions. The 1:1 output is saved at 4500 x 4500 pixels which prints 7.5 x 7.5 inch blotter sheets @ 600 dpi. Perforation marks (which can be turned off) divide the sheet into 900 quarter inch hits/tabs. When the display is put in fullscreen, the default 1:1 aspect ratio is stretched to fill the screen, but perforations are not shown. Even though the default canvas is drawn with quad symmetry, a secondary quad symmetry display can be enabled to take the blotter art to the next level. Interactive drawing functions are shown once the token is minted.

All features can be manipulated interactively using the keyboard.
- Space key or mouse click starts/stops puck drawing
- 'q' or 'Q' - secondary quad symmetry (on/off)
- 'r' or 'R' - rotate quad symmetry by 90 degrees
- 'p' or 'P' - auto pausing function (on/off)
- 'x' or 'X' - show perforations (on/off)
- 'c' or 'C' - select random puck color
- 'a' or 'A' - random color on all puck draws (on/off)
- 'b' or 'B' - color banding (on/off)
- 'm' or 'M' - puck modulation (on/off)
- 't' or 'T' - cycles transparency (none/light/medium)
- '1' - slowest (1 fps) puck drawing
- '2' - slower (10 fps) puck drawing
- '3' - faster (30 fps) puck drawing
(fps rate may not be accurate if quad symmetry enabled)
- 's' or 'S' - save 4500 x 4500 pixel png image
(print size = 7.5 x 7.5 inches @ 600 dpi)
(fullscreen saved images are screen dimensions X 2)
- 'n' or 'N' - re-initializes the gentk

Rarity features are written to the console at loading and whenever changed interactively.

March 2022
coded by StreamDreamz (a.k.a. Freakiebeat)
coded with - html, css, javascript, p5.js
